_source.rule.description: CIS Microsoft Windows 11 Enterprise Benchmark v1.0.0: Ensure 'Prevent non-admin users from installing packaged Windows apps' is set to 'Enabled'.
_source.decoder.name: sca
_source.data.sca.check.remediation: To establish the recommended configuration via GP, set the following UI path to Enabled: Computer Configuration\Policies\Administrative Templates\Windows Components\App Package Deployment\Prevent non-admin users from installing packaged Windows apps. Note: This Group Policy path may not exist by default. It is provided by the Group Policy template AppxPackageManager.admx/adml that is included with the Microsoft Windows 10 Release 2004 Administrative Templates (or newer).
_source.data.sca.check.description: This setting manages non-Administrator users' ability to install Windows app packages. The recommended state for this setting is: Enabled.
_source.data.sca.check.title: Ensure 'Prevent non-admin users from installing packaged Windows apps' is set to 'Enabled'.
_source.data.sca.check.rationale: In a corporate managed environment, application installations should be managed centrally by IT staff, not by end users.
_source.data.sca.policy: CIS Microsoft Windows 11 Enterprise Benchmark v1.0.0
